replies.body:
@Domo Gensiss - Soccer is a great sport, but it isn't nearly as popular as other sports in the USA.

Just think about where you get to watch World Cup soccer games for free at home during weekdays: Univision. If soccer was so popular, then ABC would probably have made bids against ESPN to broadcasting rights during weekdays, but guess what, it didn't. Consequently, the Olympics are more popular in the US than the World Cup, let alone your average year-round soccer match, which again you can find on Univision.

It would, however, be fair to say that soccer is a growing sport. It's just a baby. Did you know that the MLS has only been around since 1993 (21 years)? In contrast, the NBA was founded in 1946 (68 years), the NFL in 1920 (94 years) and the MLB was in 1869 (145 years).
